<item>
            <title>[LU-18967] lctl-pool_new.8 man page should list pool name constraints</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18967</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The OST pool names must be 15 or fewer alphanumeric characters (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;A-Za-z0-9&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;), and may contain hyphen (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;-&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) and underscore (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;_&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) characters.  The period (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;.&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) character may be used to separate the &lt;tt&gt;FSNAME&lt;/tt&gt; from the &lt;tt&gt;POOLNAME&lt;/tt&gt; in commands to uniquely identify the pool when multiple filesystems are mounted on a node.  The pool name must not be one of the reserved keywords &quot;&lt;tt&gt;none&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ignore&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;inherit&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#idm139621089154704&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Lustre Operations Manual&lt;/a&gt; states only that &quot;The pool name is an ASCII string up to 15 characters.&quot; and should also be updated similarly.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
